<component name="UnuAxdelete" category="UnuAtoM">
  <overview>
    <authors>
      <author>Darby Van Uitert</author>
    </authors>
    <summary>Remove one or more singleton axes from a nrrd. Singleton
axes have only a single sample along them. The underlying linear
ordering of the samples is unchanged, and the information about the
other axes is shifted downwards as needed.</summary>
    <description>
      <p>Remove one or more singleton axes from a nrrd. Singleton axes
have only a single sample along them. The underlying linear ordering
of the samples is unchanged, and the information about the other axes
is shifted downwards as needed.</p>
      <p>Axis: indicates the axis at which to delete the stub axis and
should be an integer. If you give -1 as the axis, this will do a
matlab-style squeeze, in which any and all singleton axes are
removed.</p>
    </description>
  </overview>
  <io>
    <inputs lastportdynamic="no">
      <port>
        <name>InputNrrd</name>
        <datatype>SCIRun::Nrrd</datatype>
      </port>
    </inputs>
    <outputs>
      <port>
        <name>OutputNrrd</name>
        <datatype>SCIRun::Nrrd</datatype>
      </port>
    </outputs>
  </io>
</component>


